WE AT SHAIRPORTER BELIEVE THAT THERE'S A BETTER WAY TO GET TO OR FROM THE AIRPORT ON YOUR NEXT TRIP. Living in New York, we experienced the lack of good transportation options. Taking a taxi or black town car service by yourself isn't affordable to many, especially compared to low-cost local flights. Taking the bus, shuttle, subway or train just can take twice as long with multiple stops, transfers, and set timetables. We came up with the idea of Shairporter after seeing the demand for and growth of collaborative consumption websites. If millions of people are already sharing their road-trip rides, apartments, homes, and cars, why can't we share a 30 minute taxi ride to the airport?

Full Description: Forum Analytics builds customized solutions that validate your instinct using data science to understand revenue drivers, predict performance and take a proactive approach to market planning and site selection. As an industry leader in advanced real estate analytics, Forum Analytics partners with organizations of all sizes to develop site selection and forecasting solutions to guide decisions in strategic planning. Acquired by CBRE in 2015, Forum’s breadth of data resources and integrated real estate services are unmatched in our industry. As part of CBRE, the world’s leading commercial brokerage services company, we can offer a completely integrated end-to-end real estate solution. Whether you’re looking for a standalone site selection tool or a full range of real estate services, we can provide a solution tailored to your needs. Some of our most unique attributes include: Cutting-edge solutions developed through partnerships with Google, Microsoft, StreetLight Data, NUVI, Dodge Data, Restaurant Trends, and Synergos Technologies, among others. Serving companies with units in hundreds of countries around the globe by providing both domestic and international applications, data, and services. A staff with extensive in-house experience that has been the guiding force behind the solutions we provide. Our understanding of life on the client side of the fence helps us design the most user-friendly set of tools available. Our Headquarters and Culture Forum Analytics began in Chicago and is currently located in the historic Devoe Paint Factory building in the city’s River West neighborhood. The loft design of the turn-of-the-century landmark reflects our company culture by providing a casual environment for interactive collaboration, and a space to inspire creative solutions for our clients.

Server-Side Software Development
Full Description: WebDNA Software Corporation develops and markets a server-side software called WebDNA. WebDNA is a combination of scripting language and database. The scripting language uses a simple syntax and is intuitive and easy to learn. It also incorporates a built-in database that also uses the same simple syntax. By combining the two parts of language and database, making data-driven websites and web applications is much simpler and can be accomplished in much less time. The software is compatible with most major platforms and web servers. The product was originally created by Pacific Coast Software in 1994. It was purchased by Smith Micro Software, but was not actively developed because Smith Micro was experiencing dramatic growth in their cellular operating systems division. WebDNA Software Corporation was formed in 2008 and purchased WebDNA from Smith Micro and began actively developing the product again, starting with producing a version compatible with Intel based Macintosh computers and the latest version of the Apache web server.
